Package: stmvdev
Title: Spatiotemporal models in R researching estimation and inference of complex ecosystems
Version: 2021.1
Authors@R: c( person("Jae", "Choi", email="choi.jae.seok@gmail.com", role=c("aut", "cre")) )
Description: Spatio-temporal models in R of ecosystems using constrained kernel-based approximations to estimate and develop statistical inference of space-time hierarchical models. This package interacts with other stmv*, and aegis* projects. This is the R&D additions to stmv .. mostly under testing. Requires compiler tools.
Depends: R (>= 3.0.0),
  mvtnorm,
  truncnorm
Imports:
  lubridate,
  alphahull,
  parallel,
  Rcpp,
  RcppZiggurat,
  RcppArmadillo,
  inline,
  sp,
  mgcv,
  lattice,
  geoR,
  gstat,
  fields,
  RandomFields,
  parallel,
  bigmemory,
  devtools,
  aegis,
  stmv
Suggests:
  INLA,
  biglm,
  cmdstanr,
  rmarkdown
LinkingTo:
  Rcpp,
  RcppZiggurat,
  RcppArmadillo
NeedsCompilation: yes
SystemRequirements: fftw3 (>= 3.1.2)
ByteCompile: TRUE
VignetteBuilder: knitr
License: MIT
LazyData: true
URL: https://github.com/jae0/stmv/
